result.execSummary:
The defendant Dalen J Beauprey was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Dalen J Beauprey is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Dalen J Beauprey was found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • Dalen J Beauprey was found guilty of Ordinance Violation - Bail Jumping. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

The court has no objection to transfer to another county, however must be approved by sheriff.

Good time and huber allowed.

Community service authorized under 973.03(3).

records.addlTxt: Does not plan to seek postconviction relief.
Preliminary hearing on July 9, 2014 at 03:00 pm.

Defendant Dalen J Beauprey in court with attorney John E Voorhees.  Jodie L Bednar appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 14CF63 and 13CF224. Called 10:32 am. 13CF224 return on warrant - 14CF63 INIT - has complaint waives reading - asks for PH willing to waive TL for PH. Bond continued. 13CF224 - amend count 1 to FC dc w/mv - $400 plus costs. Ct 2 plead as alleged w/hold sentence and place on probation for 2 years with costs. Ct 3 w/hold sentence and place on probation for 2 years costs conditions AODA and follow thru, sobriety , no entry consumption/poossession 100 hrs co service. Preliminary hearing scheduled for July 9, 2014 at 03:00 pm. Recalled 11:20 am. Same appearances. Now have resolution. 14CF63 Ct 1 as alleged - FC jail 30 days (2 days credit) - Ct 2 dismissed Ct 3 amend to FC ordiance BJ - $1000 inclusive. 

13CF224 Ct 1 amend FC dc w/mv pleads NC $400 plus costs - Ct 2 NC - Ct 3 mis BJ amend court reads new charges pleas NC

14CF63 Ct 2 dismiss Ct 3 amend FC bail jumping pleads NC - finds G $1000 inclusive Ct 1

Court goes thru plea and finds defendant entering freely, voluntarily and intelligently, factual basis, acceepts pleas, adjudges guility on ct 2 & 3 on 13CF244 and Ct 1 and Ct 3 as amended on 14CF63. Apply bond to all counts cases per atty and defendant. 

State final statement. Vorhees follow joint recommendation start sentence after July 4th. Beauprey apologizes.

Court sentences to following:
14 CF63 - Ct 1 30 days FC jail with 2 days credit, good time and huber, community service 973.03 (3), can serve somewhere else however sheriff must approve in both counties. Stayed jail to 6/28/14 @ 8:30 am after no objection from the state. 
13CF244 Ct 2 w/hold and place on probation for 2 years with costs and conditions of AODA and follow thru, no entry/consume/possession, 100 hrs co service. Ct 3 w/hold and place on probation 2 years with costs and same conditions no additional co service hours.
